{
  "doc_id": "27018",
  "text": "While toxicities induced by cisplatin include ototoxicity, gastrotoxicity, myelosuppression, and allergic reactions [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] the main dose-limiting side effect of cisplatin is nephrotoxicity [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Nephrotoxicity increases with the dose and frequency of administration and cumulative dose of cisplatin [CITATION_5] . As cisplatin causes nephrotoxicity, it has been suggested that the toxic effects of cisplatin may be related to free radical induced damage which can be reduced by the supplementation of antioxidants [CITATION_6] leading to the possibility that cisplatin may be used in combination with antioxidants which might suppress the drug-induced toxic effects.",
